name: Antique Trouble Light Pendant Lighting Fixture
description:
This antique trouble light was used by my Great Uncle Bob in his shop. By the time I got it, it no longer worked. But I knew that this maple handled hanging light would look great upcycled. 

So, with a new socket and 6 feet of colorful new Zig-Zag red and white cord, this no longer sits in a workshop but will look great in your kitchen, foyer or over your desk !

This fixture was assembled with new UL rated, antiqued brass finish socket. The wire is 18 gauge red and white Zig-Zag cotton pulley cord. This fixture has been shop tested (it really looked great hanging in my shop!) and is completely safe to brighten your room. 

Length is about 15"; 12-1/2" not including hook; cage is 3-3/4" wide. 

It is shown with an Edison type bulb - this IS included.

Orders are usually shipped within 1-3 business days with UPS Ground or Priority Mail, but our turnaround time can be up to 5 days.

Insurance and a tracking number are included and you will receive an email with your
tracking number when your order ships.

All orders are well packed, we reuse packing material to reduce waste and keep shipping costs low.

name: Antique Bobbin Pendant Lighting Fixture
description:
This fixture uses an antique bobbin for the handle, imitating a trouble light. 

I added a new socket and 6 feet of blue slate twisted cord and a white plug. I used the slender bulb to keep it very linear. 

I will say, that after testing it in my shop. As I held it, I felt like I was holding the very first prototype of a light saber. I'm not a big Star Wars fan, but it was kinda cool with the Edison bulb I picked out. 

This fixture was assembled with new UL rated, antiqued brass finish socket. The wire is 18 gauge Blue Slate Twisted Cloth Covered Wire. This fixture has been shop tested (it really looked great hanging in my shop!) and is completely safe to brighten your room. 

Length is about 15"; 12-1/2" not including hook; cage is 3-3/4" wide. 

It is shown with an Edison type bulb - this IS included.

We have different colors available for the cord - if you want a different color, please let me know.

name: Set of 3 Linocut Swedish Dala Horse cards, Block print
description:
My hand made Dala Horse cards feature an original hand-pulled block print on the front and are signed on the back. The cards are printed on white, acid free card stock in red water-based ink. They are packaged with envelopes. Each card measures 5 x 7 inches. They are blank inside. 

The Dala Horse (Swedish: Dalahäst) is a traditional carved and painted wooden statue of a horse originating in the Swedish province of Dalarna. In the old days the Dala horse was mostly used as a toy for children; in modern times it has become a symbol of Sweden. 

Each linocut card is hand-pulled. The cards are 5x7 100% recycled, 30% post-consumer waste paper, archival and acid-free. Each piece is hand printed by me. Due to the nature of hand printing, each print is slightly different. I design and hand carve all of my linoleum blocks.

This set includes:
3 Dala Horse cards
3 white envelopes

Please contact me if you are interested in a larger order of cards or a different color paper or ink. I would be happy to customize your order.
